
A Personal Online Desktop (POD) is a desktop that is accessible online (i.e. on the Internet). Many people argue that with the availability of cheap bandwidth, it will become unnessary for users to own their own workstations. Instead, they connect to a central server hosted on the Internet and access their applications as they would locally. This model affords users the convenience of connecting to the same desktop, independent of the device they happen to be using. There are already several companies that provide such solutions.